02 Mar 2018 21:35






I have to say, reading this left me in utter confusion. It's written well enough, but I don't know what the heck this is supposed to mean or if it's a reference, or something else. The rubber horses (that for some bizarre reason like to form wheels??) felt absolutely random and out of nowhere and didn't seem to have any relation to the rest of the anomalies. Why are people transforming into horses, or gaining horse-like features, seemingly out of nowhere? The Foundation's plan to build an SCP-2000 but specifically for horses seemed equally bizarre, and I had a hard time believing that they'd do something that extreme. I didn't really appreciate the cross-references; in my opinion, they seem somewhat tacked on, as in you looked at the Equine tag and stuffed whatever you found into the article, which, while that wouldn't necessarily be a bad thing, I don't think it works very well here. Finally, I must have missed it, but I'm not sure how exactly this counts as Hiemal anomaly, as I didn't catch anything that would point towards self-containment between any two of the anomalies, but I might have just missed it.

I gave a downvote here, because while it's written in a professional manner, I seriously have no idea what to make of this. It came off as random for random's sake from my perspective. If you were meaning to expand on this, I could easily change my vote, but right now, I can't say I can appreciate this article.





